## 4. State Management вЂ” Provider

### Architecture

Each feature area has a dedicated `ChangeNotifier` class registered via `MultiProvider` at the app root.

```mermaid
graph LR
    subgraph "ChangeNotifiers"
        A1["AuthProvider"]
        A2["UserProvider"]
        D1["EmployeeProvider"]
        D2["AttendanceProvider"]
        D3["SettingsProvider"]
    end

    subgraph "Widgets"
        W1["Consumer / context.watch"]
        W2["Selector"]
    end

    A1 --> A2
    A2 --> D1
    A2 --> D2
    W1 --> A1
    W1 --> D1
    W2 --> D2
```

| ChangeNotifier | Responsibility |
|---|---|
| `AuthProvider` | Wraps `FirebaseAuth`, exposes `currentUser`, `login()`, `logout()`, `isAdmin` |
| `UserProvider` | CRUD on `users` collection, employee list stream |
| `EmployeeProvider` | Dedicated notifier for employee list filtering & management (Admin) |
| `AttendanceProvider` | Punch-in/out, daily attendance stream, history queries, date filtering |
| `SettingsProvider` | App settings (work start time, late threshold, Telegram config) |

### Registration in `main.dart`

```dart
runApp(
  MultiProvider(
    providers: [
      ChangeNotifierProvider(create: (_) => AuthProvider()),
      ChangeNotifierProxyProvider<AuthProvider, UserProvider>(
        create: (_) => UserProvider(),
        update: (_, auth, userProv) => userProv!..updateAuth(auth),
      ),
      ChangeNotifierProxyProvider<AuthProvider, AttendanceProvider>(
        create: (_) => AttendanceProvider(),
        update: (_, auth, attProv) => attProv!..updateAuth(auth),
      ),
      ChangeNotifierProvider(create: (_) => SettingsProvider()),
    ],
    child: const App(),
  ),
);
```

