## 9. FCM Push Notifications

| Step | Detail |
|---|---|
| 1 | Add `firebase_messaging` package |
| 2 | Request notification permission on app start |
| 3 | Store device FCM token in `users/{uid}.fcmToken` |
| 4 | On punch-in/out, optionally send a push via the FCM HTTP v1 API (requires a service account key, called from the Flutter app or a Cloud Function) |

> For the free tier, we'll send Telegram messages directly from the client. FCM is optional and can be layered on with Cloud Functions later.

